# Git workflow

After finishing a user task that changed the repo:

1. Run `git status` and include all relevant changes (no `.env` or secrets).
2. Commit with a clear English message describing why.
3. Push to `origin` on the current branch (`git push -u origin HEAD` if no upstream).

Do this in the same session before reporting done, unless the user asked not to push or there is nothing to commit.
